Singapore
Publish Start Date
Mar 26 2014
Job Level
Experienced (Non-Manager)
|
Responsibilities:
Responsible for managing Project from the receipt of order up to delivery.
Conduct Kick off Meetings, generate schedule, progress reporting (internal & customer) and change order managements.
Responsible for leading cross - functional pursuit team, CSR team, buyer, planner and managing project orders.
Lead technical discussions and engineering status reviews with customers; support the Project Manager on large multi-divisional projects.
Work closely with internal functional groups to execute orders and maximize service levels, reduces FG and customer satisfaction goals while adding profitability to the company.
Requirements:
Diploma/Degree in Mechanical, Instrument, Electronic or Chemical Engineering with 3 to 5 years of experience in Process Instrumentation or related industry.
Prior experience as an Instrument & Controls Engineer would be advantageous.
Instrument Project Execution experience would be added advantage.